I can see 136 rdfs:label entries with trailing whitespace. Let me write a   
  script to fix them all.

Progress update: Initial plan for label_whitespace fix

[ ] Strip trailing whitespace from all 136 rdfs:label values in efo-edit.owl
  (NMR metabolomics terms in EFO_0022xxx range, cell lines like TPC-1, BON-1, 
  MES-23.5, and one term with a non-breaking space)                           
  [ ] Run make normalize_src to normalize the ontology file                   
  [ ] Run parallel validation

Bash: Strip trailing whitespace from rdfs:label values
$ python3 -c "                                                            
    import re                                                                 
                                                                              
    input_file = '/home/runner/work/efo/efo/src/ontology/efo-edit.owl'        
    output_file = '/home/runner/work/efo/efo/src/ontology/efo-edit.owl'       
                                                                              
    with open(input_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:                        
        content = f.read()                                                    
                                                                              
    # Replace rdfs:label content that has trailing whitespace/non-breaking-   
  space before closing tag                                                    
    # This handles regular spaces and non-breaking spaces (\xa0)              
    fixed, count = re.subn(                                                   
        r'(<rdfs:label(?:[^>]*)>)(.*?)[\s\xa0]+(</rdfs:label>)',              
        lambda m: m.group(1) + m.group(2).rstrip(' \t\xa0') + m.group(3),     
        content                                                               
    )                                                                         
                                                                              
    print(f'Fixed {count} labels')                                            
                                                                              
    with open(output_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:                       
        f.write(fixed)                                                        
    "                                                                         
                                                                              
    Fixed 136 labels                                                          
    <exited with exit code 0>


